The imposition of a penalty was threatened, but never implemented. MTI was placed in liquidation in December 2020 after the company failed to honour requests for withdrawals by some of the 200 000-plus members. Chief Executive Officer Johann Steynberg stopped answering calls and disappeared to Brazil, where he was arrested earlier this year. An estimated 29 000 Bitcoin, worth more than $1 billion at current prices, are reckoned to have been channelled through the scheme. --Moneyweb-- 